data.headline: Dow and Russell 2000 outperform in early premarket trading while Nasdaq 100 dips slightly
bullets: Traders position cautiously ahead of the delayed January Non-Farm Payrolls report, with consensus at +70K jobs
Market focus remains on implications of jobs data for upcoming Fed rate-cut decisions
US dollar slips as yen and Australian dollar strengthen, reflecting shifting currency sentiment
Bond markets flash warnings about the US economic outlook
Premarket attention centers on NVDA, HOOD, MRNA, ASTS, and earnings from McDonald's, T-Mobile, and Shopify, with no major surprises reported
